    "Options include trabeculectomy or glaucoma drainage device implantation.",
    "These surgeries aim to create a new pathway for aqueous humor to leave the eye, thereby reducing IOP.",
    "The choice between these options would depend on the specifics of the case, including the severity of the glaucoma, the eye's anatomy, and the surgeon's experience and preference 2.",
    "Aniridia and Zonular Instability Management: The absence of the iris (aniridia) and partial loss of zonules can contribute to the patient's symptoms of glare and photophobia, as well as potentially complicate intraocular surgeries.",
    "Custom artificial iris devices could be considered for implantation to reduce these symptoms and improve cosmetic appearance."
